                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A living creature steps on any part of the floor not enclosed by the summoning circle</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> One round after a creature touches the triggering area, the door to the room slams shut and locks (two <span data-pf2-action=\"pickALock\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-glyph=\"D\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span> checks to pick) and a @Compendium[pf2e.pathfinder-bestiary.Barbazu]{Barbazu} devil appears in the summoning circle.</p>\n<p>The devil rolls initiative and remains for [[/br 3d6 #rounds]]{3d6 rounds}, after which the spell ends and the devil disappears. The devil also disappears if someone disables the trap before the duration expires.</p>\n<p>The summoned devil can use 3 actions each round and can use reactions, unlike most summoned creatures.</p>"
